================================================================================
Bundled evaluation data: parallel/
================================================================================

The files under parallel/ (parallel/<iso639-3>_<Script>.txt) are derived from
the FLORES+ dataset and are used here for tokenizer evaluation only.

  Dataset:  FLORES+ (Open Language Data Initiative)
  Source:   https://huggingface.co/datasets/openlanguagedata/flores_plus
  License:  CC-BY-SA 4.0 (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/)

Because this data is distributed under CC-BY-SA 4.0, redistribution (including
the copies in this repository) is under the same license, with attribution.
FLORES+ is intended for evaluation, not as training data.

FLORES+ asks users to cite the original FLORES papers, in particular:
  NLLB Team et al. "Scaling neural machine translation to 200 languages."
  Nature 630 (2024).

The file parallel/_mapping_report.txt records how FineWeb2 language codes were
mapped to FLORES+ configuration names. Six files use a FLORES+ configuration
whose code differs from the filename (for example cmn_Hani.txt holds cmn_Hans,
fas_Arab holds pes_Arab, mni_Mtei holds mni_Beng); see that report for the full
list.

================================================================================
Third-party tokenizers referenced in examples
================================================================================

Example configurations may reference tokenizers from the Hugging Face Hub or
from tiktoken. Those tokenizers are downloaded at run time from their
respective sources and are not redistributed in this repository. The bundled
sample tokenizers (tokenizers/bpe.json, tokenizers/unigramlm.json) are small
BPE and Unigram tokenizers included only to run the demo.
